%% ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
%%  EBS Pub/Sub — Fault Tolerance Sequence Diagram
%%  Shows broker failure detection and subscription recovery
%% ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant B1 as broker-1
    participant B2 as broker-2 (will fail)
    participant B3 as broker-3
    participant S as Subscriber

    Note over B1,B3: NORMAL OPERATION (every 2s)
    B1->>B2: Heartbeat
    B1->>B3: Heartbeat
    B2->>B1: Heartbeat
    B2->>B3: Heartbeat
    B3->>B1: Heartbeat
    B3->>B2: Heartbeat

    Note over B2: At any time, each broker replicates<br/>new subscriptions to peers
    S->>B2: Subscription
    B2->>B1: BrokerState(replicate subscription)
    B2->>B3: BrokerState(replicate subscription)

    Note over B2: t=10s: broker-2 CRASHES
    B2--xB2: process killed

    Note over B1,B3: t=10s to t=40s — no heartbeats from broker-2
    loop every 2s
        B1->>B1: lastHeartbeat[broker-2] = 8s ago...<br/>then 10s, 20s, 30s
        B3->>B3: same observation
    end

    Note over B1,B3: t=40s: timeout (30s) exceeded
    B1->>B1: ⚠ broker-2 marked DEAD<br/>router.removeBroker("broker-2")
    B3->>B3: ⚠ broker-2 marked DEAD<br/>router.removeBroker("broker-2")

    Note over B1,B3: Absorb replicated subscriptions
    B1->>B1: absorbFailedBroker(broker-2)<br/>→ takes over predicates for fields<br/>previously owned by broker-2
    B3->>B3: same

    Note over S,B3: System continues delivering notifications
    Note over B1,B3: All "variation" and "date" predicates<br/>now handled by broker-1 or broker-3<br/>(based on new consistent hash)
